<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,423,1206]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,423,449]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[430,527,423,450]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4–8 mm</quantity>
. Shiny yellow to dark brown (sometimes ferruginous) or black. Palpus ventrally convex, axe-shaped. Arista bare. Cell 
<emphasis box="[587,627,460,485]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">cup</emphasis>
(anal cell of most micropezid literature) long (CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1223,1231,478,492]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">2</subScript>
as long or longer than A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[225,233,514,528]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">1</subScript>
+CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[302,310,514,528]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">2</subScript>
). Wing membrane around the anterior part of dm-cu unpigmented (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1134,495,521]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1671]" captionTargetId="figure-162@4.[151,1436,453,1671]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. 1, Paragrallomyia citrina n. sp. wing. Arrow: unpigmented membrane around the anterior part of dm-cu; 2, Taeniaptera trivittata (Fabricius) wing and male genitalia, distiphallus. Abbreviations: ddp—Distal distiphallus, dsc—Discal band, stg—Stigmatal band." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401192/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, except in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferro &amp; Marshall, 2020" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[287,350,531,557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[287,350,531,557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[437,463,549,563]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">4+5</subScript>
almost always open at the wing margin, closed only in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1085,1343,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpes">
<emphasis box="[1085,1343,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia vulpes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,423,1206]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,567,593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[345,524,567,593]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[345,524,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[842,1006,567,593]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Taeniapterinae">Taeniapterinae</taxonomicName>
with a long cell 
<emphasis box="[1198,1238,568,593]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">cup</emphasis>
(CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1308,1316,586,600]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">2</subScript>
as long or longer than A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[305,313,622,636]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">1</subScript>
+CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[382,390,622,636]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">2</subScript>
) and an axe-shaped palpus by a characteristic patch of unpigmented wing membrane around the anterior part of dm-cu (
<figureCitation box="[457,523,639,665]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1671]" captionTargetId="figure-162@4.[151,1436,453,1671]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. 1, Paragrallomyia citrina n. sp. wing. Arrow: unpigmented membrane around the anterior part of dm-cu; 2, Taeniaptera trivittata (Fabricius) wing and male genitalia, distiphallus. Abbreviations: ddp—Distal distiphallus, dsc—Discal band, stg—Stigmatal band." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401192/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The genus is further characterized by a narrowed distal distiphallus and a basal distiphallus that is twice as wide as the distal distiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[805,884,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. Paragrallomyia albibasis (Enderlein). 6, female, dorsal view; 7, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view; 8, female, Costa Rica, dorso-lateral view; 9, male internal reproductive structures, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401198/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Figs. 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[896,926,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1774,1798]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,741,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-263@14.[151,1437,741,1751]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Paragrallomyia colombiana n. sp. 20, female, dorsal view; 21, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view; 22, male, lateral view; 23, copulatory fork and internal reproductive structures with taxonomically significant structures. Abbreviations: bdp—Basal distiphallus, ddp—Distal distiphallus, ea—Ejaculatory apodeme, ep—Epandrium, fa—Fork arm, hy—Hypandrium, il—Inner basal lobes, pb—Phallic bulb, ph—Phallapodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401210" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401210/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[938,968,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–34" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,489,1404]" captionTargetId="figure-146@19.[151,1436,489,1404]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 31–34. Paragrallomyia nodulosa n. sp. 31, female, dorsal view; 32, female internal reproductive structures, lateral view; 33, male, lateral view; 34, copulatory fork and internal reproductive structures, ventral and lateral view, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401222" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401222/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[980,1010,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–38" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-186@20.[151,1436,525,1592]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 35–38. Paragrallomyia pseudoalbibasis n. sp. 35, female, dorsal view; 36, female internal reproductive structures, lateral view; 37, Costa Rica, dorsal view; 38, copulatory fork and internal reproductive structures, ventral and lateral view, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401224" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401224/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1022,1053,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–42" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1056,1080]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-29@22.[151,1436,166,1040]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 39–42. Paragrallomyia quadrifurca n. sp. 39, female, dorsal view; 40, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view; 41, male, lateral view; 42, copulatory fork and internal reproductive structures, ventral and lateral view, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401226/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">42</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1064,1095,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–46" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1336,1360]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,344,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-72@23.[151,1436,344,1312]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 43–46. Paragrallomyia quaternaria n. sp. 43, female, dorsal view; 44, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view; 45, male, lateral view; 46, male internal reproductive structures, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401230/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">46</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1106,1136,675,702]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–52" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1440,1464]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1417]" captionTargetId="figure-208@28.[151,1436,597,1417]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 49–52. Paragrallomyia thiemei (Enderlein). 49, female, dorsal view; 50, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view; 51, male, Ecuador, lateral view; 52, copulatory fork and internal reproductive structures, ventral and lateral view, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401235/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">52</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1148,1180,675,702]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–56" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,777,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-270@29.[151,1436,777,1865]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 53–56. Paragrallomyia vulpes (Cresson). 53, female, dorsal view; 54, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view; 55, male, dorsolateral view; 56, male, internal reproductive structures, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401239/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">56</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,423,1206]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[199,333,712,737]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Taeniaptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,333,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Taeniaptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species also have an axe-shaped palpus but are distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[1120,1299,711,737]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1120,1299,711,737]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pigmented wing membrane around dm-cu and by the wide (as wide as basal distiphallus), heavily sclerotized distal distiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[295,363,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1671]" captionTargetId="figure-162@4.[151,1436,453,1671]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. 1, Paragrallomyia citrina n. sp. wing. Arrow: unpigmented membrane around the anterior part of dm-cu; 2, Taeniaptera trivittata (Fabricius) wing and male genitalia, distiphallus. Abbreviations: ddp—Distal distiphallus, dsc—Discal band, stg—Stigmatal band." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401192/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). We here propose 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[575,709,784,809]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Taeniaptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,709,784,809]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Taeniaptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a small group of two named species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1154,1390,783,810]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Taeniaptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lasciva">
<emphasis box="[1154,1260,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">T. lasciva</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Macquart)" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" box="[151,413,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Taeniaptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivittata">
<emphasis box="[151,277,820,845]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">T. trivittata</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</taxonomicName>
, and at least two undescribed species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,423,1206]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
The following species, treated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[581,760,855,881]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[581,760,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, M. D. &amp; Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H." box="[805,1045,855,882]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref24750" refString="Jackson, M. D., Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H. (2015) Molecular phylogeny of the Taeniapterini (Diptera: Micropezidae) using nuclear and mitochondrial DNA, with a reclassification of the genus Taeniaptera Macquart. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 46, 1 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 45032125" type="journal article" year="2015">
Jackson 
<emphasis box="[902,960,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
, lack the derived characters of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[229,408,891,917]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,408,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as redefined here: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Enderlein)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Enderlein" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[642,936,891,918]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeripennis">
<emphasis box="[642,793,892,917]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. aeripennis</emphasis>
(Enderlein)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Albuquerque)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Albuquerque" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[952,1246,891,918]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliceae">
<emphasis box="[952,1066,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. aliceae</emphasis>
(Albuquerque)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Enderlein)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Enderlein" baseAuthorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilutimacula">
<emphasis box="[1262,1437,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. dilutimacula</emphasis>
(Enderlein)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wulp)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Wulp" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[293,516,927,954]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifascia">
<emphasis box="[293,425,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. latifascia</emphasis>
(Wulp)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cresson)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Cresson" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[527,732,927,953]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauta">
<emphasis box="[527,614,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. lauta</emphasis>
(Cresson)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hendel)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[744,998,927,954]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longifurca">
<emphasis box="[744,888,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. longifurca</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Macquart)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[1009,1291,927,953]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis box="[1009,1155,928,953]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. nigritarsis</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Macquart)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufifacies">
<emphasis box="[1302,1436,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. rufifacies</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Czerny)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Czerny" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[291,520,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seiuncta">
<emphasis box="[291,410,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. seiuncta</emphasis>
(Czerny)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hendel)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[530,770,963,990]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[530,661,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. simillima</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Enderlein)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Enderlein" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[781,1032,963,990]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigata">
<emphasis box="[781,895,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. strigata</emphasis>
(Enderlein)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Macquart)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1042,1282,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[1042,1147,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. tibialis</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Coquillett)" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittipennis">
<emphasis box="[1293,1437,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. vittipennis</emphasis>
(Coquillett)
</taxonomicName>
. Only one of these species, 
<emphasis box="[596,710,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Albuquerque" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[596,707,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliceae">P. aliceae</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
was sequenced in 
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, M. D. &amp; Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H." box="[920,1156,999,1026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref24750" refString="Jackson, M. D., Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H. (2015) Molecular phylogeny of the Taeniapterini (Diptera: Micropezidae) using nuclear and mitochondrial DNA, with a reclassification of the genus Taeniaptera Macquart. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 46, 1 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 45032125" type="journal article" year="2015">
Jackson 
<emphasis box="[1016,1072,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
, and this species was out of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[220,399,1035,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[220,399,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade in their analysis. These species fit better in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hennig" authorityName="Hennig" authorityYear="1934" box="[944,1170,1035,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[944,1082,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Poecilotylus</emphasis>
Hennig
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[1257,1436,1035,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1436,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Paragrallomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and are transferred there as new combinations with the full realization that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hennig" authorityYear="1934" box="[1006,1144,1071,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1144,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Poecilotylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently just a repository for Taeniapterini that do not fit into better defined genera. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Enderlein)" baseAuthorityName="Enderlein" box="[851,1204,1107,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Taeniaptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata">
<emphasis box="[851,1070,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Taeniaptera lineata</emphasis>
(Enderlein)
</taxonomicName>
is also transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hennig" authorityYear="1934" box="[151,289,1143,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,289,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Poecilotylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as reference to the 
<typeStatus box="[505,553,1144,1170]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
specimen shows a parallel-sided palpus. A list of all species currently placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hennig" authorityYear="1934" box="[151,289,1179,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Poecilotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,289,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Poecilotylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be found in 
<tableCitation box="[529,612,1179,1205]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,151,175]" captionText="TABLE 1. Paragrallomyia and Poecilotylus species, including new nomenclatural changes." pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
